column5: Last week the walleye moved out to the main lake, humps were loaded, especially ones that topped out between 15'' to 20' feet deep, although one reef that topped out at 8' held a few decent slot fish.https://youtu.be/-omXzsexmjY
Looks like good fishing. Thanks for the great video.

Nice video! I've fished Wabigoon/Dinorwic 3 times and have always struggled finding non dink walleyes. We've caught a bunch, but always have to weed through the little ones. I need to follow you around lol.

Sounds pretty much like my beloved Wabigoon, every now and then you get a nice one or even a bunch of slot fish, but a lot of 15-18Â” ers. It's getting better with the new slot, and Covid gave it a bit of a break too.
